Addresses feedback from PR #9 regarding incorrect middleware pipeline ordering.

## Changes

- Moved `UseRouting()` call before `UseStaticFiles()` to follow ASP.NET Core middleware ordering conventions
- Pipeline now follows recommended order: `UseRouting()` → `UseStaticFiles()` → `UseAuthentication()` → `UseAuthorization()` → endpoint mapping

```csharp
app.UseHttpsRedirection();

// Setup routing first, as per ASP.NET Core middleware ordering best practices
app.UseRouting();

// Configure static file serving
app.UseStaticFiles();
app.UseStaticFiles(new StaticFileOptions { ... });

app.UseAuthentication();
app.UseAuthorization();
```

Previously, routing was configured after static files, which can lead to unexpected behavior with endpoint routing.

